  - `docs/presentation/` — Slides and script for the 8-minute presentation
  - `docs/roadmap.md` — Active roadmap (analysis-focused, 15 tasks)
  - `docs/roadmap_implementation.md` — Archived implementation-focused roadmap
  - `docs/roadmap_replication.md` — Full 10-game replication roadmap (reference)

## Virtual Environment

- The venv lives at `.venv/` in the project root.
- Always use `.venv/bin/python` or activate with `source .venv/bin/activate`.
- AXIOM and Gameworld are installed from `vendor/` in editable mode.
- Install new analysis dependencies by adding them to `pyproject.toml` then `pip install -e ".[dev]"`.

## Running Things

- AXIOM experiments are run from `vendor/axiom/` using `python main.py --game=X --param=Y`.
- Sweep scripts in `experiments/` automate multi-configuration runs.
- Use `make` targets: `make baseline`, `make sweep-phase1`, `make figures`, etc.
- Set `WANDB_MODE=disabled` to suppress wandb prompts during runs.

## Coding Conventions

- Python 3.10+, formatted with ruff (line length 100).
- Analysis code uses numpy, scipy, pandas, matplotlib, seaborn.
- AXIOM itself uses JAX, equinox, jaxtyping (do not modify AXIOM source except for BMR logging).
- Type hints on public function signatures.
- Tests use pytest.

## Roadmap

- The task breakdown is in `docs/roadmap.md` (15 tasks across 5 phases).
- To start a task, read the roadmap entry for the task number and follow its instructions.
- Check `docs/replication_log.md` first to see what has already been completed.
- Phases 1-3 are independent analysis themes; they can be done in any order.

