- This file is shared memory across sessions for both human and LLM agents.

## Key Paper Details

- Four mixture models: sMM (slots from pixels), iMM (object identity), tMM (dynamics modes),
  rMM (object interactions + reward/action).
- Most use conjugate priors (NIW, Dirichlet, Gamma); the tMM uses flat priors with fixed covariance.
- All use truncated stick-breaking priors for automatic model expansion.
- Inference: coordinate-ascent VI, one frame at a time (streaming), gradient-free.
- Structure learning: online growing heuristic + BMR every 500 frames.
- BMR: samples rMM components, scores mutual expected log-likelihoods on ancestrally-generated
  data, and greedily merges if it decreases expected free energy of reward/tMM-switch multinomials.
- Planning: active inference with expected free energy (utility + information gain).
- Benchmark: Gameworld 10k — 10 games, 10k steps, 10 seeds.

## Class Project (CS 677)

This repo fulfills a CS 677 Bayesian Methods final project consisting of:

- Presentation (40 pts) — 8-min async video on Discord, slides in `docs/presentation/`
- Peer Review (10 pts) — review classmates' presentations
- Report (40 pts) — 4–5 pages, 12pt, 1in margins, single-spaced, in `docs/report/`

The report audience is a fellow CS 677 student. Key grading dimensions:
background material, connection to Bayesian inference, discussion/interpretation
of results, writing clarity, and the presentation itself.

Compile the report with `make report` from `docs/report/`.
